<p>Find all complex solutions to the equation:</p>

<p>$$ x^{4}+x^{3}+2 x^{2}+x+1=0 $$</p>


Sol.

<p>It is easy to see that $x^{4}+x^{3}+2 x^{2}+x+1=\left(x^{2}+1\right)\left(x^{2}+x+1\right)$.</p>


