<p>(a) Count the number of roots $w$ of the equation $z^{2019}-1=0$ over complex numbers that satisfy $|w+1| \geq \sqrt{2+\sqrt{2}}$</p>

Sol.

<p>Such roots can be expressed as follows</p>

<p>$$ w=\frac{\cos (2 \pi k)}{2019}+i \frac{\sin (2 \pi k)}{2019} \quad \text { for } k=0,\pm 1, \ldots,\pm 1009 $$</p>

<p>Therefore,</p>

<p>$$ |w+1|^{2}=2+2 \frac{\cos (2 \pi k)}{2019} $$</p>

<p>Hence we want to ident if $\mathrm{y} k$ such $\mathrm{that}$</p>

<p>$$ \frac{\cos (2 \pi k)}{2019} \geq \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} $$</p>

<p>Which is equivalent to</p>

<p>
$$
\begin{array}{l}
\quad\left|\frac{2 \pi k}{2019}\right| \leq \frac{\pi}{4} \\
\text { i.e. }|k| \leq 252
\end{array}
$$
</p>

<p>So there are 505 solutions satisfying the given inequality.</p>



